segments.text: We have unfortunately seen the right wing use trigger laws to attack abortion rights around the country, which we have strenuously opposed.

segments.text: In the case of rent control, I think it is extremely essential that this kind of trigger law be passed in Seattle in order to lend major momentum and much needed momentum for a statewide movement to force the state legislature to repeal the ban on rent control.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: The rent control policy my office is proposing has none of the corporate loopholes that the landlord lobby has often used to undermine and nullify rent control protections in cities and states across the world.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: I'll go into more detail about each of these during the committee meeting this Friday, and we'll just summarize them now.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: The rent control policy from my office caps rent increases at no more than the rate of inflation.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: Landlords can choose to raise the rent less than the rate of inflation
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: reduce the rent or keep it the same, but they may not raise it more than inflation.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: All the rental housing in Seattle will be protected.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: In some cities, rent control only applies to certain rental homes, and you have to be very lucky to get a rent control apartment.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: In our policy, all renters will be protected.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: There is no vacancy decontrol in this rent control policy.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: Some cities have created a loophole where landlords can raise the rent by however much they want anytime a renter moves.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: This is what vacancy decontrol is.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: This means that the rent control policy becomes far less effective in keeping rents affordable citywide.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: It also creates those outrageous situations where an unscrupulous landlord will try and bully a renter out of their apartment in order to raise the rents.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: There is one-to-one replacement of affordable units anytime there is new construction in this proposed policy from my office.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: So which means that if a developer demolishes a 10 unit building to build a 100 unit building, the new landlords need to maintain the rents of the 10 units they demolished using some of the new units.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: There will be a rent control board deal with exceptions.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: So if a small landlord faces unforeseen costs like a tree falling on the roof and they really need financial support,
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: There will be a rent control board that can grant exceptions, but those are only for when an exception is really needed.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: We will go into more detail about this at the committee on Friday.
